diagnoses_procedures_extraction.template:
Extract DIAGNOSES and PROCEDURES from the following medical record context.

IMPORTANT: Pay close attention to dates!

{context}

CRITICAL: You MUST return a JSON OBJECT with this EXACT structure:

{
  "diagnoses": [
    {
      "name": "diagnosis name",
      "icd_code": "ICD code or null",
      "type": "primary/secondary/admitting/discharge",
      "date": "MM/DD/YYYY or null",
      "status": "active/resolved/chronic"
    }
  ],
  "procedures": [
    {
      "name": "procedure name",
      "date": "MM/DD/YYYY or null",
      "provider": "performing provider or null",
      "location": "where performed or null",
      "findings": "results/findings or null",
      "complications": "complications or null"
    }
  ]
}

CRITICAL INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Extract dates! Convert to MM/DD/YYYY format.
2. Include ALL items mentioned.
3. Return ONLY valid JSON. Do not include any text before or after the JSON object.
